Health Department Minister Zweli Mkhize is briefing the media on the latest COVID-19 updates. On Friday, Mkhize announced that South Africa had 2 783 confirmed cases of coronavirus with 50 deaths. In the video below, Mkhize briefs the media:  For more information you can call the coronavirus 24-hour hotline on 0800 029 999. You can also add the official government COVID-19 support service on WhatsApp on 0600 123 456. Health Minister Dr Mkhize has reiterated the importance of staying at home to help to fight the coronavirus. “The possibility of the infection spreading whilst we are on the lockdown is high if you do not stay at home. Actually, it can be self-defeating to have a lockdown but people actually continue to mingle and in the process spread the infection.”